22VideoCodecVP8 VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp8Settings() {
23 VideoCodecVP8 vp8_settings;
24 memset(&vp8_settings, 0, sizeof(vp8_settings));
25
26 vp8_settings.numberOfTemporalLayers = 1;
27 vp8_settings.denoisingOn = true;
28 vp8_settings.automaticResizeOn = false;
29 vp8_settings.frameDroppingOn = true;
30 vp8_settings.keyFrameInterval = 3000;
31
32 return vp8_settings;
33}

86bool VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits::operator==(
87 const ResolutionBitrateLimits& rhs) const {
88 return frame_size_pixels == rhs.frame_size_pixels &&
89 min_start_bitrate_bps == rhs.min_start_bitrate_bps &&
90 min_bitrate_bps == rhs.min_bitrate_bps &&
91 max_bitrate_bps == rhs.max_bitrate_bps;
92}

94VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::EncoderInfo()
95 : scaling_settings(VideoEncoder::ScalingSettings::kOff),
96 requested_resolution_alignment(1),
97 apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers(false),
98 supports_native_handle(false),
99 implementation_name("unknown"),
100 has_trusted_rate_controller(false),
101 is_hardware_accelerated(true),
102 has_internal_source(false),
103 fps_allocation{absl::InlinedVector<uint8_t, kMaxTemporalStreams>(
104 1,
105 kMaxFramerateFraction)},
106 supports_simulcast(false),
107 preferred_pixel_formats{VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420} {}

113std::string VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::ToString() const {
114 char string_buf[2048];
115 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder oss(string_buf);
116
117 oss << "EncoderInfo { "
118 "ScalingSettings { ";
119 if (scaling_settings.thresholds) {
120 oss << "Thresholds { "
121 "low = "
122 << scaling_settings.thresholds->low
123 << ", high = " << scaling_settings.thresholds->high << "}, ";
124 }
125 oss << "min_pixels_per_frame = " << scaling_settings.min_pixels_per_frame
126 << " }";
127 oss << ", requested_resolution_alignment = " << requested_resolution_alignment
128 << ", apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers = "
129 << apply_alignment_to_all_simulcast_layers
130 << ", supports_native_handle = " << supports_native_handle
131 << ", implementation_name = '" << implementation_name
132 << "'"
133 ", has_trusted_rate_controller = "
134 << has_trusted_rate_controller
135 << ", is_hardware_accelerated = " << is_hardware_accelerated
136 << ", has_internal_source = " << has_internal_source
137 << ", fps_allocation = [";
138 bool first = true;
139 for (size_t i = 0; i < fps_allocation->size(); ++i) {
140 if (!first) {
141 oss << ", ";
142 }
143 const absl::InlinedVector<uint8_t, kMaxTemporalStreams>& fractions =
144 fps_allocation[i];
145 if (!fractions.empty()) {
146 first = false;
147 oss << "[ ";
148 for (size_t i = 0; i < fractions.size(); ++i) {
149 if (i > 0) {
150 oss << ", ";
151 }
152 oss << (static_cast<double>(fractions[i]) / kMaxFramerateFraction);
153 }
154 oss << "] ";
155 }
156 }
157 oss << "]";
158 oss << ", resolution_bitrate_limits = [";
159 for (size_t i = 0; i < resolution_bitrate_limits.size(); ++i) {
160 if (i > 0) {
161 oss << ", ";
162 }
163 ResolutionBitrateLimits l = resolution_bitrate_limits[i];
164 oss << "Limits { "
165 "frame_size_pixels = "
166 << l.frame_size_pixels
167 << ", min_start_bitrate_bps = " << l.min_start_bitrate_bps
168 << ", min_bitrate_bps = " << l.min_bitrate_bps
169 << ", max_bitrate_bps = " << l.max_bitrate_bps << "} ";
170 }
171 oss << "] "
172 ", supports_simulcast = "
173 << supports_simulcast;
174 oss << ", preferred_pixel_formats = [";
175 for (size_t i = 0; i < preferred_pixel_formats.size(); ++i) {
176 if (i > 0)
177 oss << ", ";
178 oss << VideoFrameBufferTypeToString(preferred_pixel_formats.at(i));
179 }
180 oss << "]";
181 oss << "}";
182 return oss.str();
183}
184
185bool VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::operator==(const EncoderInfo& rhs) const {
186 if (scaling_settings.thresholds.has_value() !=
187 rhs.scaling_settings.thresholds.has_value()) {
188 return false;
189 }
190 if (scaling_settings.thresholds.has_value()) {
191 QpThresholds l = *scaling_settings.thresholds;
192 QpThresholds r = *rhs.scaling_settings.thresholds;
193 if (l.low != r.low || l.high != r.high) {
194 return false;
195 }
196 }
197 if (scaling_settings.min_pixels_per_frame !=
198 rhs.scaling_settings.min_pixels_per_frame) {
199 return false;
200 }
201
202 if (supports_native_handle != rhs.supports_native_handle ||
203 implementation_name != rhs.implementation_name ||
204 has_trusted_rate_controller != rhs.has_trusted_rate_controller ||
205 is_hardware_accelerated != rhs.is_hardware_accelerated ||
206 has_internal_source != rhs.has_internal_source) {
207 return false;
208 }
209
210 for (size_t i = 0; i < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++i) {
211 if (fps_allocation[i] != rhs.fps_allocation[i]) {
212 return false;
213 }
214 }
215
216 if (resolution_bitrate_limits != rhs.resolution_bitrate_limits ||
217 supports_simulcast != rhs.supports_simulcast) {
218 return false;
219 }
220
221 return true;
222}
223
224absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits>
225VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(
226 int frame_size_pixels) const {
227 std::vector<ResolutionBitrateLimits> bitrate_limits =
228 resolution_bitrate_limits;
229
230 // Sort the list of bitrate limits by resolution.
231 sort(bitrate_limits.begin(), bitrate_limits.end(),
232 [](const ResolutionBitrateLimits& lhs,
233 const ResolutionBitrateLimits& rhs) {
234 return lhs.frame_size_pixels < rhs.frame_size_pixels;
235 });
236
237 for (size_t i = 0; i < bitrate_limits.size(); ++i) {
238 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].min_bitrate_bps, 0);
239 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].min_start_bitrate_bps, 0);
240 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].max_bitrate_bps,
241 bitrate_limits[i].min_bitrate_bps);
242 if (i > 0) {
243 // The bitrate limits aren't expected to decrease with resolution.
244 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].min_bitrate_bps,
245 bitrate_limits[i - 1].min_bitrate_bps);
246 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].min_start_bitrate_bps,
247 bitrate_limits[i - 1].min_start_bitrate_bps);
248 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bitrate_limits[i].max_bitrate_bps,
249 bitrate_limits[i - 1].max_bitrate_bps);
250 }
251
252 if (bitrate_limits[i].frame_size_pixels >= frame_size_pixels) {
253 return absl::optional<ResolutionBitrateLimits>(bitrate_limits[i]);
254 }
255 }
256
257 return absl::nullopt;
258}

260VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters::RateControlParameters()
261 : bitrate(VideoBitrateAllocation()),
262 framerate_fps(0.0),
263 bandwidth_allocation(DataRate::Zero()) {}

265VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters::RateControlParameters(
266 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate,
267 double framerate_fps)
268 : bitrate(bitrate),
269 framerate_fps(framerate_fps),
270 bandwidth_allocation(DataRate::BitsPerSec(bitrate.get_sum_bps())) {}
271
272VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters::RateControlParameters(
273 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate,
274 double framerate_fps,
275 DataRate bandwidth_allocation)
276 : bitrate(bitrate),
277 framerate_fps(framerate_fps),
278 bandwidth_allocation(bandwidth_allocation) {}
279
280bool VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters::operator==(
281 const VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters& rhs) const {
282 return std::tie(bitrate, framerate_fps, bandwidth_allocation) ==
283 std::tie(rhs.bitrate, rhs.framerate_fps, rhs.bandwidth_allocation);
284}

287 const VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters& rhs) const {
288 return !(rhs == *this);
289}

296int32_t VideoEncoder::InitEncode(const VideoCodec* codec_settings,
297 int32_t number_of_cores,
298 size_t max_payload_size) {
299 const VideoEncoder::Capabilities capabilities(/* loss_notification= */ false);
300 const VideoEncoder::Settings settings(capabilities, number_of_cores,
301 max_payload_size);
302 // In theory, this and the other version of InitEncode() could end up calling
303 // each other in a loop until we get a stack overflow.
304 // In practice, any subclass of VideoEncoder would overload at least one
305 // of these, and we have a TODO in the header file to make this pure virtual.
306 return InitEncode(codec_settings, settings);
307}
308
309int VideoEncoder::InitEncode(const VideoCodec* codec_settings,
310 const VideoEncoder::Settings& settings) {
311 // In theory, this and the other version of InitEncode() could end up calling
312 // each other in a loop until we get a stack overflow.
313 // In practice, any subclass of VideoEncoder would overload at least one
314 // of these, and we have a TODO in the header file to make this pure virtual.
315 return InitEncode(codec_settings, settings.number_of_cores,
316 settings.max_payload_size);
317}
